exchanges.description:
Calculated value according to literature: 
ES(CH4) = 0.670 x Bo x C(OM) x EF1 x t
where ES(CH4) is the methane emissions in kg CH4/t of wet substrate;
Bo = 0.345 is the substrate methane emission potential in m3 CH4/kg OM;
C(OM) is the average organic-matter content of the substrates in kg OM/t of wet substrate;
This is calculated (980.1 kg OM/t of wet substrate) by multiplying the DM of the substrate (0.99% on wet mass basis) with the OM content (0.99% OM on a dry matter basis).
EF1 = 10% is the methane emission factor;
t is the percentage of the time that the substrate is stored at the biogas producer’s (0.1, supposed that the substrates are stored at the biogas producer’s for 10% of the stockage time before digestion)
The value includes emissions from the storage of the substrate until its use from the anaerobic digestion process but also emissions from the storage of the digestate until its final use. 

Reference:
Dauriat A., Gaillard G., Alig M., Scharfy D., Membrez Y., Bachmann N., Steiner R., Charles R., Maltas A., Sinaj S., Analyse de cycle de vie de la production centralisée et décentralisée de biogaz en exploitations agricoles : Rapport final. Hrsg. Station de recherche Agroscope Reckenholz-Tänikon ART & Station de recherche Agroscope Changins-Wädenswil ACW, Zürich et Nyon. Avril, 2012, 1-147 S.
